<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Mission Trip Safety for Churches & Mission Organizations -- SafeTrekr</title>
  <meta name="description" content="SafeTrekr assigns a professional safety analyst to review every mission trip your church sends -- across 17 dimensions of risk. Government intelligence. Audit-ready documentation. Starting at $450 per trip.">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Mission Trip Safety Built for Faith-Based Organizations">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Professional analyst review, government intelligence, and tamper-evident documentation for every mission trip. Starting at $450.">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://safetrekr.com/solutions/churches">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="design-tokens.css">
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
  <script>
    tailwind.config = {
      theme: {
        extend: {
          colors: {
            background: '#e7ecee',
            foreground: '#061a23',
            card: '#f7f8f8',
            border: '#b8c3c7',
            ring: '#365462',
            muted: { DEFAULT: '#e7ecee', foreground: '#4d5153' },
            primary: {
              50: '#f1f9f4', 100: '#e0f1e6', 200: '#c0e2cd', 300: '#96cfac',
              400: '#6cbc8b', 500: '#4ca46e', 600: '#3f885b', 700: '#33704b',
              800: '#2a5b3d', 900: '#20462f', 950: '#132a1c',
              DEFAULT: '#3f885b', foreground: '#ffffff'
            },
            secondary: {
              DEFAULT: '#123646', foreground: '#f7f8f8',
              light: '#1a4a5e', muted: '#b8c3c7'
            },
            destructive: { DEFAULT: '#c1253e', foreground: '#ffffff' },
            safety: { green: '#22c55e', yellow: '#eab308', red: '#ef4444' },
            dark: {
              surface: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.1)',
              'text-primary': '#f7f8f8',
              'text-secondary': '#b8c3c7',
              accent: '#6cbc8b'
            }
          },
          fontFamily: {
            heading: ['Plus Jakarta Sans', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            body: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            mono: ['JetBrains Mono', 'ui-monospace', 'monospace']
          },
          maxWidth: {
            'container': '1280px'
          }
        }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: BreadcrumbList -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Solutions", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Churches & Mission Organizations", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions/churches" }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: FAQPage -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do we need SafeTrekr for domestic mission trips too?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. A domestic mission trip still involves transporting volunteers -- often including minors -- to unfamiliar locations. Your duty of care obligation does not depend on whether you cross a border." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does SafeTrekr handle international destinations with limited infrastructure?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our analyst reviews specifically account for infrastructure gaps. When a destination has limited emergency medical facilities, unreliable communication networks, or poor road conditions, those factors are documented in the binder." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can our volunteer trip leader use this without training?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Trip submission is a guided 10-step wizard that takes 15-20 minutes. Your trip leader enters destinations, dates, venues, team members, and transportation details. Our analyst handles the rest." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does our insurance carrier receive?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Your insurance carrier receives the same safety binder your church board reviews -- a complete 17-section analyst report with government intelligence data, venue safety assessments, emergency preparedness documentation, and a tamper-evident audit trail." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How quickly do we get the safety binder back?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "3-5 business days from trip submission to binder delivery. For churches planning mission trips months in advance, this timeline fits naturally into your preparation schedule." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can SafeTrekr handle multi-stop mission trips?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Many mission trips involve multiple cities, venues, and lodging locations. Our analyst reviews each stop independently. Each destination gets its own risk intelligence assessment." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is SafeTrekr appropriate for youth group trips?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Absolutely. Youth group trips carry heightened duty of care obligations because you are transporting minors. SafeTrekr's review includes factors specifically relevant to youth safety." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does pricing work for multiple trips per year?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each trip is priced independently -- $450 for domestic, $750 for domestic overnight, $1,250 for international. Churches booking 5 or more trips per year qualify for volume pricing." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What if our denomination already has safety guidelines?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SafeTrekr complements and strengthens your denominational safety requirements. Most denominational guidelines provide a framework -- SafeTrekr provides the documented execution." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you offer background check services for mission trip volunteers?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. SafeTrekr offers background checks as an add-on service at $35 per person. These can be integrated into your trip preparation workflow." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What happens if conditions change after we receive the binder?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Your safety analyst monitors conditions for active trips. During your mission trip, your team receives morning and evening safety briefings covering weather changes, transit advisories, local events, and overnight developments." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can church board members access the safety binder directly?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. You control access to the safety binder. It can be shared as a PDF with your church board, insurance committee, denominational leadership, or anyone else who needs to review your safety preparation." }}
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    /* ── Page-level overrides & enhancements ── */

    /* Dot grid background pattern */
    .bg-dot-grid {
      background-image: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-border) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 24px 24px;
    }

    /* Sticky in-page nav */
    .page-nav {
      position: sticky;
      top: 72px;
      z-index: 20;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      transform: translateY(-100%);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, opacity 0.3s ease;
    }
    .page-nav.visible {
      transform: translateY(0);
      opacity: 1;
    }
    .page-nav-inner {
      overflow-x: auto;
      -ms-overflow-style: none;
      scrollbar-width: none;
      scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    }
    .page-nav-inner::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
    .page-nav-link {
      scroll-snap-align: start;
      white-space: nowrap;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
      border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .page-nav-link:hover { color: var(--color-foreground); }
    .page-nav-link.active {
      color: var(--color-primary-700);
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary-500);
    }

    /* Accordion */
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .faq-trigger {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      width: 100%;
      padding: 20px 0;
      background: none;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      text-align: left;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.25rem);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--color-foreground);
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .faq-trigger:hover { color: var(--color-primary-700); }
    .faq-trigger svg {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }
    .faq-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }
    .faq-content {
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
    }
    .faq-content.open {
      max-height: 800px;
    }
    .faq-content-inner {
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 0.875rem + 0.15vw, 1rem);
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
    }

    /* Hero visual composition */
    .hero-visual {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 520px;
    }
    .hero-map {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 4/3;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d4dce0 0%, #c8d3d8 40%, #bcc8ce 100%);
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }
    .hero-map svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
    .hero-binder-card {
      position: absolute;
      top: -16px;
      right: -16px;
      width: 260px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .hero-status-badge {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 24px;
      left: 16px;
    }

    /* Binder preview stack */
    .binder-stack { position: relative; width: 100%; max-width: 360px; padding: 20px; }
    .binder-page {
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 24px;
      position: absolute;
      width: 100%;
    }
    .binder-page-back {
      transform: rotate(-2deg) translate(-12px, -16px);
      opacity: 0.7;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }
    .binder-page-mid {
      transform: rotate(-1deg) translate(-6px, -8px);
      opacity: 0.9;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    }
    .binder-page-front {
      position: relative;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
    }

    /* Comparison table layout */
    .comparison-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .comparison-row {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 0;
      }
      .comparison-item + .comparison-item {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-top: 16px;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }
    }

    /* Feature card link arrow hover */
    .feature-card:hover .arrow-icon {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .arrow-icon {
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    /* Site header */
    .site-header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 30;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.95);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    /* Smooth scroll */
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      html { scroll-behavior: auto; }
    }

    /* Counter animation */
    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
    .animate-fade-up {
      animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease forwards;
    }

    /* Mobile menu */
    .mobile-menu { display: none; }
    .mobile-menu.open { display: flex; }

    /* Pricing card highlight */
    .pricing-card-highlight {
      position: relative;
      border-color: var(--color-primary-400);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md), 0 0 0 1px var(--color-primary-200);
    }
  </style>
<script src="https://mcp.figma.com/mcp/html-to-design/capture.js" async></script>
</head>
<body class="font-body" style="background: var(--color-background); color: var(--color-foreground);">

  <!-- Skip navigation -->
  <a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:bg-white focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded-md focus:shadow-lg focus:text-primary-700 focus:font-semibold focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring">
    Skip to main content
  </a>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       SITE HEADER
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <header id="site-header" class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-30 transition-all duration-300" style="height: 80px;">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 h-full flex items-center justify-between">
      <!-- Logo: Horizontal lockup -->
      <a href="/" aria-label="SafeTrekr home" class="flex-shrink-0">
        <svg height="32" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hidden lg:block" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
        <svg height="28" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg:hidden" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
      </a>

      <!-- Desktop Nav -->
      <nav aria-label="Main navigation" class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-8">
        <a href="/platform" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Platform
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/solutions" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Solutions
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/how-it-works" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">How It Works</a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/resources" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Resources
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </nav>

      <!-- Desktop CTAs -->
      <div class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-4">
        <a href="https://app.safetrekr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sm font-semibold transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-foreground" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Sign In</a>
        <a href="/demo" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center font-semibold rounded-md transition-all duration-150 text-white" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); background: var(--color-primary-600); padding: 10px 20px; font-size: 15px; border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none;">Get a Demo</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Mobile Hamburger -->
      <button id="mobile-menu-btn" class="lg:hidden p-2 text-foreground" aria-label="Open navigation menu" aria-expanded="false">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h16"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       IN-PAGE NAVIGATION (Sticky, appears on scroll)
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <nav id="page-nav" class="page-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
    <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">
      <div class="page-nav-inner flex items-center lg:justify-center gap-0">
        <a href="#challenge" class="page-nav-link" data-section="challenge">The Challenge</a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="page-nav-link" data-section="how-it-works">How It Works</a>
        <a href="#sample-binder" class="page-nav-link" data-section="sample-binder">Sample Binder</a>
        <a href="#pricing" class="page-nav-link" data-section="pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="#compliance" class="page-nav-link" data-section="compliance">Security</a>
        <a href="#faq" class="page-nav-link" data-section="faq">FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       MAIN CONTENT
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────
         SECTION 1: HERO
         ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="hero" aria-label="Hero" style="background: var(--color-background);" class="pt-8 pb-12 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-16 md:pt-16 md:pb-20 lg:pt-20 lg:pb-28 xl:pt-28 xl:pb-36">
      <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">

        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 lg:mb-8">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
            <li><a href="/" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Home</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li><a href="/solutions" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Solutions</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li aria-current="page" class="font-medium" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Churches &amp; Mission Organizations</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
          <!-- Text Column -->
          <div>
            <!-- Eyebrow -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-5">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">MISSION TRIP SAFETY</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Headline -->
            <h1 class="text-display-xl max-w-[20ch]" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
              Your Mission Team Deserves a Safety Analyst
            </h1>

            <!-- Subheadline -->
            <p class="text-body-lg mt-6 max-w-[50ch]" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
              SafeTrekr brings the same professional safety review that Fortune 500 companies use for business travel to every mission trip your church sends. Government intelligence. 17-section analyst review. Audit-ready documentation your insurance carrier and church board can trust.
            </p>

            <!-- CTAs -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
              <a href="/resources/sample-binders/mission-trip" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                Download Mission Trip Sample Binder
              </a>
              <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-lg btn-secondary">
                Get a Demo
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual Column -->
          <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="hero-visual">
              <!-- Map Fragment -->
              <div class="hero-map">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 480 360" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <!-- Desaturated map background -->
                  <rect width="480" height="360" fill="#d4dce0"/>
                  <!-- Water -->
                  <path d="M0 180 Q120 160 200 200 Q280 240 360 180 Q420 140 480 160 V360 H0 Z" fill="#c0cdd3" opacity="0.5"/>
                  <!-- Land masses -->
                  <path d="M40 80 Q80 60 140 90 Q180 110 200 80 Q240 50 300 70 Q340 85 360 120 Q320 150 280 140 Q240 130 200 150 Q160 170 120 140 Q80 110 40 80Z" fill="#bcc8ce"/>
                  <path d="M300 160 Q340 140 380 170 Q420 200 440 180 Q460 160 480 190 V280 Q460 260 420 250 Q380 240 340 260 Q300 280 280 240 Q260 200 300 160Z" fill="#b0bec5"/>
                  <!-- Route path -->
                  <path d="M140 120 Q200 140 260 130 Q320 120 380 180" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="8 4" fill="none" opacity="0.8"/>
                  <!-- Waypoint: departure -->
                  <circle cx="140" cy="120" r="8" fill="white" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                  <circle cx="140" cy="120" r="3" fill="var(--color-primary-500)"/>
                  <!-- Waypoint: destination -->
                  <circle cx="380" cy="180" r="8" fill="white" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                  <circle cx="380" cy="180" r="3" fill="var(--color-primary-500)"/>
                  <!-- Labels -->
                  <text x="115" y="108" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="var(--color-muted-foreground)">Houston, TX</text>
                  <text x="360" y="205" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="var(--color-muted-foreground)">Guatemala City</text>
                </svg>
              </div>

              <!-- Binder Preview Card -->
              <div class="hero-binder-card hidden sm:block">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">International Mission Trip</span>
                </div>
